# MEETING SCHEDULING & ROUTING
# =============================================================================
CATEGORY_CONTENT["meeting-scheduling"] = {
 "definition": "automate the process of booking, routing, and managing sales meetings through calendar links, intelligent lead routing, round-robin assignment, and CRM integration. These tools eliminate the back-and-forth emails that delay meetings and ensure leads reach the right rep instantly.",
 "definition_expanded": "Scheduling tools range from simple calendar link generators (Calendly) to sophisticated lead routing engines that qualify inbound leads in real time, match them to the right rep based on territory, account ownership, or round-robin rules, and book the meeting without any human intervention. The revenue impact is significant: every hour of delay between form submission and meeting booking reduces conversion rates by 10-20%. The best scheduling tools compress that gap to under a minute.",
 "buying_guide": "Simple scheduling links work fine for freelancers and small teams. If all you need is a shareable booking page with calendar sync and Zoom integration, Calendly or SavvyCal at $10-$15/month per user handles it well. The ROI of more expensive tools comes from speed-to-lead for inbound and intelligent routing for teams with complex assignment rules.\n\nInbound lead routing is where the category gets interesting for sales teams. Tools like Chili Piper and RevenueHero sit on your website forms and demo request pages, qualifying leads in real time and presenting a booking widget immediately after submission. This eliminates the delay between form fill and meeting, which is the single biggest lever for improving inbound conversion rates. If your team processes more than 50 inbound demo requests per month, the conversion lift from instant booking typically pays for the tool within the first quarter.\n\nRound-robin fairness and routing complexity matter as your team grows. Simple round-robin assigns meetings to reps in order. More sophisticated routing considers territory rules, account ownership in the CRM, rep capacity, and lead scoring. If a prospect from an existing account submits a form, the meeting should route to the account owner, not the next rep in the rotation. Evaluate how each tool handles these edge cases because they compound as your team scales. Also confirm that the tool updates your CRM automatically, creating contacts, logging activities, and associating meetings with the correct opportunity.",
 "faqs": [
 {"question": "How much does slow meeting booking cost in lost revenue?", "answer": "Research from Chili Piper and other vendors shows that conversion rates drop 10-20% for every hour of delay between an inbound request and a booked meeting. The average B2B company takes 42 hours to respond to a demo request. Companies using instant scheduling report 2-3x higher inbound conversion rates compared to manual follow-up. For a team generating 100 inbound leads per month, that difference translates to 15-30 additional meetings."},
 {"question": "What is the difference between Calendly and Chili Piper?", "answer": "Calendly is a scheduling link tool that lets anyone book time on your calendar. Chili Piper is an inbound lead routing and scheduling platform that qualifies and routes leads from web forms to the right rep in real time. Calendly is simpler and cheaper ($10/month per user). Chili Piper is built for sales teams that need instant routing, round-robin, and CRM integration ($15-$45/month per user for the scheduling product)."},
 {"question": "How does round-robin scheduling work?", "answer": "Round-robin distributes incoming meetings evenly across a team of reps. Basic round-robin assigns in sequential order. Weighted round-robin accounts for rep capacity or performance. Smart round-robin considers territory rules, account ownership, and availability. Most tools also support pooled availability, showing prospects the combined open slots of all eligible reps to maximize booking options."},
 {"question": "Do scheduling tools integrate with Salesforce and HubSpot?", "answer": "All major scheduling tools integrate with Salesforce and HubSpot. The depth of integration varies. Basic integrations log the meeting as an event. Advanced integrations create or update contacts, associate meetings with opportunities, update lead status, and trigger workflow automations. Chili Piper and RevenueHero have the deepest CRM integrations for sales use cases. Calendly's CRM integration is functional but less customizable."},
 {"question": "Should I use my CRM's built-in scheduling or a dedicated tool?", "answer": "HubSpot's built-in meeting scheduler is solid for basic use cases and saves you an additional subscription. Salesforce does not include native scheduling. Dedicated tools offer better lead routing, faster form-to-meeting conversion, and more flexibility for complex team structures. If you have a simple team (under 10 reps, no territory rules, mostly outbound), CRM-native scheduling works fine. For inbound-heavy teams with complex routing needs, a dedicated tool pays for itself."},
 ],
}

